-- Brazil's BTG Pactual mulls sale of hybrid notes to boost capital
-- By Guillermo Parra-Bernal
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 12:21PM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, Aug 6 (Reuters) - Grupo BTG Pactual SA <BBTG11.SA>, Latin America's largest independent investment bank, is considering the sale of hybrid instruments to bolster its capital position, Chief Executive Officer Andre Esteves said on Wednesday.   (Reporting by Guillermo Parra-Bernal; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)  ((guillermo.parra@thomsonreuters.com; +55-11-5644-7714; +55-119-8346-7153; Reuters Messaging: guillermo.parra.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: BTGPACTUAL RESULTS/ISSUANCE

